# Day 02 - Semantic HTML & Forms

## Goal for Today

- Learn semantic HTML
- Understand forms
- Build a registration page

## What I Learned
Focus was writing cleaner and more meaningful HTML.

Topics covered:

- Semanctic elements
- `<header>`
- `<nav>`
- `<main>`
- `<section>`
- `<article>`
- `<footer>`
- HTMl forms
- Labels
- Input types
- Validation attributes
- Buttons

I learned why semantic HTML improves accessibility and search engine optimization. Using descriptive tags also make code easier to understand.
